# ai-lib-plans Sync Automation Rules

## Rule 1 — Sync Before Planning

Before drafting or updating planning documents in `ai-lib-plans`, run:

`bash /home/alex/ai-lib-plans/tools/sync_ai_lib_plans.sh --mode pre-plan`

If sync fails, stop planning work and resolve sync/conflict issues first.

## Rule 2 — Sync After Documentation Changes

When documentation files in `ai-lib-plans` are changed and committed, push to **`lan`** (primary, GOV-004):

`git push lan main`

Optional mirror to GitHub hiddenpath: `git push origin main`

On Linux/WSL (legacy path): `bash /home/alex/ai-lib-plans/tools/sync_ai_lib_plans.sh --mode post-doc-change --push-if-ahead`

This keeps local and remote repositories synchronized after document updates.

## Rule 3 — Mandatory Final Step for Implementation Plans

For every implementation plan/task execution managed in `ai-lib-plans`, the final mandatory step is:

1. Backfill task/plan execution status and result fields (e.g., `status`, `testing`, `completion_notes`, `updated`, and related evidence fields).
2. Push **`ai-lib-plans` to `lan`** (mandatory during GOV-004 trial): `git push lan main`

Optional GitHub backup: `git push origin main`

If the sync/push step fails, execution is not considered fully closed.
